---
import DefaultLayout from '@layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'
import booklet from '@assets/images/booklet.png'
import { Link } from 'accessible-astro-components'
import Experience from '@components/Experience.astro'
import KeyStrengths from '@components/KeyStrengths.astro'
---

<DefaultLayout title="About Ilias">
  <section class="hero my-24">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 items-center gap-24 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-8 md:items-start">
          <h1 class="text-center text-6xl md:text-left">Ilias says hi! ðŸ‘‹</h1>
          <p>
            I was born 11 months after the web, and it took me a decade to discover it. Thirteen years later, I found
            myself working at the web's birthplace, CERN.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've been privileged to work most of my career on open-source projects. These days I work remotely as the
            lead maintainer of several user-facing apps at <Link href="https://alephium.org">Alephium</Link>.
          </p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl">The beginning</h2>
          <p>
            My first experience with programming came at the age of 11. My parents sent me to a computer class after
            school hours. There, I learned programming with Logo, a language similar to Lisp. We would draw shapes on
            the screen by giving commands to a "turtle".
          </p>
          <p>
            There, I also surfed the web for the fist time. When Iâ€™d finish my homework early, my teacher would allow me
            to use the IE5. Oh boy, such fun! I had a tiny booklet with a catalogue of all the websites I knew.
          </p>
          <Image
            src={booklet}
            alt="Notebook with a catalogue of all the websites I knew"
            width={600}
            height={450}
            class="h-auto w-full max-w-sm"
            sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 20rem, (min-width: 768px) 18rem, 100vw"
          />
          <p>
            In highschool, I picked the pseudo-programming class, and eventually decided to study computer science at
            the Aristotle University of Thessaloniki.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="my-24">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-12 text-4xl font-bold">Experience</h2>
      <Experience />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="my-24">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-12 text-4xl font-bold">Key Strengths</h2>
      <KeyStrengths />
    </div>
  </section>
</DefaultLayout>
